The paper deals with the design of efficient algorithms for fundamental graph problems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a novel multivariate approach for solving weighted parameterized problems, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of parameterized complexity theory and the analysis of running times suggest that it could also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The fact that the paper deals with graph problems and their optimization suggests that it could belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the use of combinatorial optimization techniques and the analysis of solution sizes suggest that it could also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
